{ A discovered attack occurs when a piece moves and unmasks an attack from a piece behind it — the moving piece creates a second threat simultaneously. A discovered check is especially powerful since the opponent must address the check first. }
1. Ne5+ { Correct. The Knight checks and at the same time discovers an attack on the Queen. Black has to answer the check by moving the King, and so loses the Queen. } { [%cal Gf1f8,Ge5d7] } 1... Ke7 { Of course Black protects the Queen so as to retake. } 2. Rxf8 { Of course. White wins the Queen for his Rook. After Black recaptures, White is ahead a Knight. White should then capture the Black pawns with his Knight and King being careful to keep the Knight pawn so as to avoid any possibility of a draw.
- Have you internalized the Knight's move?
- Do you see indirect attacks such as the Rook's indirect attack on the Black Queen in the initial position?
- Can you win this endgame against the strongest opposition? } *


