[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ This is the second of the Lichess Discovery exercises. This is similar to the previous chapter with the Queen and King swapped. }
1. Ne5+ { Correct. The Knight attacks the Queen and discovers an attack by the Rook on the King. This is called a Discovered Check. } { [%cal Ge5d7,Gf1f8] } 1... Ke7 { Black moves to recapture on d7. } 2. Nxd7 { After Black recaptures, White is ahead a Rook. White wins easily because the King and Rook can mate alone and Black has no counter-play.
- Have you internalized the Knight's move?
- Do you see indirect attacks such as the Rook's indirect attack on the Black King in the initial position?
- Can you win this endgame against the strongest opposition? } *


